<ul>
<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/ballmer-goes-punching-last-microsoft-employee-meeting-010354048--sector.html' target="_blank">Ballmer goes out punching at last Microsoft employee meeting</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/ballmer-goes-punching-last-microsoft-employee-meeting-010354048--sector.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/oMH6WeGR2_tKK3FujMZpHQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-09-27T010354Z_1_CBRE98Q030K00_RTROPTP_2_MICROSOFT-BUILD.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="Microsoft CEO Ballmer gestures during his keynote address at the Microsoft &quot;Build&quot; conference in San Francisco" align="left" title="Microsoft CEO Ballmer gestures during his keynote address at the Microsoft &quot;Build&quot; conference in San Francisco" border="0" /></a>By Bill Rigby SEATTLE (Reuters) - Microsoft Corp Chief Executive Steve Ballmer took his farewell bow before thousands of applauding employees on Thursday with a typically loud and emotional performance at his last companywide meeting, talking up the software giant&#039;s prospects and taking swipes at rivals. The CEO, whose screeching and dancing at company events is the stuff of YouTube legend, stormed the stage to &quot;Can&#039;t Hold Us&quot; by Seattle rap/producer duo Macklemore and Ryan Lewis, and kept up his usual high tempo, according to several people present at the employee-only meeting. </p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/yahoo-backs-alibabas-management-ipo-debate-goes-070939872--finance.html' target="_blank">Yahoo backs Alibaba's management as IPO debate goes on</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/yahoo-backs-alibabas-management-ipo-debate-goes-070939872--finance.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Rm7aMcqDQkjDpLUpv4P25w--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-09-27T070939Z_1_CBRE98Q0JW800_RTROPTP_2_YAHOO.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="The Yahoo logo is shown at the company&#039;s headquarters in Sunnyvale" align="left" title="The Yahoo logo is shown at the company&#039;s headquarters in Sunnyvale" border="0" /></a>HONG KONG (Reuters) - Yahoo Inc joined Japan&#039;s SoftBank Corp on Friday in backing Alibaba Group Holding Ltd&#039;s planned partnership structure. The U.S. Internet company, Alibaba&#039;s second-largest shareholder with a 24 percent stake, said it&#039;s important for technology companies to be able to preserve their culture and strategy. </p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/jack-ma-keep-tight-grip-alibaba-ipo-004507045--finance.html' target="_blank">How Jack Ma can keep a tight grip on Alibaba after an IPO</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/jack-ma-keep-tight-grip-alibaba-ipo-004507045--finance.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/xzdQ4OCR8SXG5DJmMsoK9Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-09-27T004507Z_1_CBRE98Q024600_RTROPTP_2_CBUSINESS-US-ALIBABA-STRUCTURE.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="File of Jack Ma, chairman of China&#039;s largest e-commerce firm Alibaba Group attending a corporate event at the company&#039;s headquarters on the outskirts of Hangzhou, Zhejiang province" align="left" title="File of Jack Ma, chairman of China&#039;s largest e-commerce firm Alibaba Group attending a corporate event at the company&#039;s headquarters on the outskirts of Hangzhou, Zhejiang province" border="0" /></a>By Olivia Oran and Alexei Oreskovic NEW YORK/SAN FRANCISCO (Reuters) - Alibaba Group Holding Ltd founder Jack Ma wants to keep a tight grip on the Chinese e-commerce company he founded even after he takes it public, and U.S. law gives him several ways to do so. The company had planned to list in Hong Kong, but the exchange there threw cold water on Ma&#039;s plan to give Alibaba&#039;s insiders, who only own about 10 percent of the stock, the power to nominate a majority of the board, sources say. Regulators in the Chinese territory said that all shareholders must be treated equally. </p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/blogs/upgrade-your-life/how-to-strip-ads-from-your-facebook-newsfeed-143136582.html' target="_blank">How to Strip Ads from your Facebook Newsfeed</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/blogs/upgrade-your-life/how-to-strip-ads-from-your-facebook-newsfeed-143136582.html"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/4.lE52DVAI.KHvffdtDc5A--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://l.yimg.com/os/publish-images/news/2013-09-25/d479e5bb-c443-4c96-b6ef-b9d0a0cdb0bc_uyl_fbADS_thumb.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Facebook ads" align="left" title="Facebook ads" border="0" /></a>New tricks and tools to control the advertisements on your Facebook pages.</p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/ea-settles-ncaa-student-athlete-cases-no-game-025740186--sector.html' target="_blank">EA settles NCAA student-athlete cases, no game next year</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/ea-settles-ncaa-student-athlete-cases-no-game-025740186--sector.html"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/7T7j6JKBDyCfVATszBOGNQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-09-27T025740Z_2_CBRE98P1L0300_RTROPTP_2_CONSOLES-GAMESCOM.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="An overview shows the Electronic Arts EA exhibition stand during the Gamescom 2013 fair in Cologne" align="left" title="An overview shows the Electronic Arts EA exhibition stand during the Gamescom 2013 fair in Cologne" border="0" /></a>By Malathi Nayak SAN FRANCISCO (Reuters) - Electronic Arts said it had reached a settlement with former college football athletes who have accused the company of using their images without permission and would not be making a new game for the popular &quot;NCAA Football&quot; series in 2014. The athletes sued the video game publisher and the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA), which has strict rules prohibiting them from sharing in the millions of dollars that schools receive from television and licensing deals. The case against the NCAA is still pending. </p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/softbank-ceo-son-says-very-supportive-alibabas-partnership-021619782--sector.html' target="_blank">Softbank CEO Son says 'very supportive' of Alibaba's partnership</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/softbank-ceo-son-says-very-supportive-alibabas-partnership-021619782--sector.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/OMzTExSr0INW6.6WZ8D6Pw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-09-27T021619Z_1_CBRE98Q06BG00_RTROPTP_2_CBUSINESS-US-ALIBABA-SOFTBANK.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="Softbank Corp President Masayoshi Son speaks during a news conference in Tokyo" align="left" title="Softbank Corp President Masayoshi Son speaks during a news conference in Tokyo" border="0" /></a>HONG KONG/TOKYO (Reuters) - Softbank Corp CEO Masayoshi Son said on Friday the company fully supports a partnership system in Chinese e-commerce giant Alibaba Group Holding Ltd. The group of 28 partners in Alibaba include the company&#039;s founder Jack Ma, some of Alibaba&#039;s senior managers and other insiders. Alibaba, which is preparing for an initial public offering valued at up to $15 billion, is looking to keep top management decisions within the partner group by giving it the right to nominate a majority of board members in the company. </p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/blackberrys-heins-fairfaxs-watsa-55-million-handshake-225920540--finance.html' target="_blank">BlackBerry's Heins, Fairfax's Watsa and the $55 million handshake</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/blackberrys-heins-fairfaxs-watsa-55-million-handshake-225920540--finance.html"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/TmyRc0U2koj2TpWwyw3GHQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-09-26T232707Z_1_CBRE98P1RVM00_RTROPTP_2_BLACKBERRY-AGM.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="BlackBerry Chief Executive Thorsten Heins speaks at the company&#039;s annual meeting in Waterloo" align="left" title="BlackBerry Chief Executive Thorsten Heins speaks at the company&#039;s annual meeting in Waterloo" border="0" /></a>By Alastair Sharp TORONTO (Reuters) - Months before Fairfax Financial Holdings Inc bid $4.7 billion for BlackBerry Ltd, Fairfax boss Prem Watsa played a role in securing a golden parachute worth as much as $55 million for the smartphone maker&#039;s chief executive, according to company filings. Watsa, Fairfax&#039;s chief executive, joined BlackBerry&#039;s board in January 2012 and was one of three directors charged in March with reviewing the compensation of the Canadian company&#039;s chief executive, Thorsten Heins. </p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://www.androidapps.com/tech/articles/13721-new-android-apps-worth-downloading-vintique-jackthreads-galaxy-defense' target="_blank">New Android apps worth downloading: Vintique, JackThreads, Galaxy Defense</a><br />
Today brings us fashionable photography, fashionable clothing, and a very fashionable new tower defense game. Vintique lets you take your photos to the next level with dozens of gorgeous filters and effects. JackThreads lets you access great deals on fashionable clothing from their site, assuming you're a member. And Galaxy Defense adds some much needed style and substance to the stagnant tower defense genre.
<li><a href='http://www.engadget.com/2013/09/27/voltaic-switch-solar-bag-tablets?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000589' target="_blank">Voltaic Switch solar bag powers your tiny tablets with sunlight</a><br />
<p><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/09/27/voltaic-switch-solar-bag-tablets?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000589"><img src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/m0Z.QT.Bm7_Eez2Ed7Ed0g--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Engadget/voltaic-switch-hed.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="DNP Voltaic solar bag for tablets" align="left" title="DNP Voltaic solar bag for tablets" border="0" /></a>Powers up to 80 minutes of iPad Mini runtime for every hour in the sun.</p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://www.theverge.com/2013/9/27/4776074/youtube-comments-makeover-upsets-stephen-colbert' target="_blank">Stephen Colbert incites spam assault on YouTube's spam assault</a><br />
<p><a href="http://www.theverge.com/2013/9/27/4776074/youtube-comments-makeover-upsets-stephen-colbert"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/enamOAi.Jwzvzaz0fuxUwg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_US/News/The%20Verge/Clipboard02_large.png" width="130" height="86" alt="Stephen Colbert incites spam assault on YouTube&#039;s spam assault" align="left" title="Stephen Colbert incites spam assault on YouTube&#039;s spam assault" border="0" /></a>Stephen Colbert isn&#039;t happy with YouTube&#039;s upcoming comment section makeover, as proved in this snippet from his show. The satirist argues that by tying a comment to its writer&#039;s Google+ account and highlighting only worthy discussions inside a video&#039;s comments, YouTube is committing an &quot;unprecedented attack on free speech.&quot;</p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://www.theverge.com/2013/9/27/4776120/ipcc-climate-change-report-says-man-to-blame-for-global-warming' target="_blank">Humans are 'extremely likely' the cause of global warming, says landmark UN report</a><br />
<p><a href="http://www.theverge.com/2013/9/27/4776120/ipcc-climate-change-report-says-man-to-blame-for-global-warming"><img src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/.PnMByTg7J2v68edu9GePA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_US/News/The%20Verge/theverge3_1020_large.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Humans are &#039;extremely likely&#039; the cause of global warming, says landmark UN report" align="left" title="Humans are &#039;extremely likely&#039; the cause of global warming, says landmark UN report" border="0" /></a>A UN panel of climate change experts today announced that mankind is almost certainly to blame for global warming, warning that the planet will see increasingly extreme weather events unless governments take strong action. In a much anticipated report released Friday, the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) said it is &quot;extremely likely&quot; that most global warming is manmade, asserting its claims with 95 percent certainty.</p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://www.engadget.com/2013/09/26/evernote-expands-with-new-product-line?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000589' target="_blank">Evernote expands with new product line: scanners, Post-Its, wallets and socks</a><br />
