<li><a href='http://news.yahoo.com/top-shareholders-back-alibabas-controversial-corporate-structure-071310343--sector.html' target="_blank">Top shareholders back Alibaba's controversial corporate structure</a><br />
<p><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/top-shareholders-back-alibabas-controversial-corporate-structure-071310343--sector.html"><img src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Q.q_NhbZiDGyEdQ0qBNv7w--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2013-09-27T071310Z_1_CBRE98Q0K2600_RTROPTP_2_CBUSINESS-US-ALIBABA-IPO.JPG" width="130" height="86" alt="File of employees standing on a logo of Alibaba (China) Technology Co. Ltd during a media tour organised by government officials at its headquarters on the outskirts of Hangzhou" align="left" title="File of employees standing on a logo of Alibaba (China) Technology Co. Ltd during a media tour organised by government officials at its headquarters on the outskirts of Hangzhou" border="0" /></a>(Reuters) - Alibaba Group&#039;s biggest shareholders have backed a partnership structure that is at the center of a debate over where the Chinese e-commerce giant may list its shares in the most highly anticipated Internet IPO since Facebook Inc&#039;s $16 billion offer last year. Alibaba, which analysts value at as much as $120 billion, appears to have failed to convince Hong Kong regulators to waive tough listing rules, potentially handing the lucrative IPO to rival U.S. market operators. </p><br clear="all"/>
<li><a href='http://www.engadget.com/2013/09/26/google-gives-search-a-new-engine-and-card-ui-outs-new-ios-searc?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000589' target="_blank">Google gives search a new engine and card UI for mobile, reveals new iOS search app</a><br />
<p><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/09/26/google-gives-search-a-new-engine-and-card-ui-outs-new-ios-searc?ncid=txtlnkusaolp00000589"><img src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/j1dCWebl5pFKpE33EOoCuQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7Zmk9ZmlsbDtoPTg2O3E9ODU7dz0xMzA-/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Engadget/dsc05653.jpg" width="130" height="86" alt="Google gives search a new engine and card UI for mobile, reveals new iOS search app" align="left" title="Google gives search a new engine and card UI for mobile, reveals new iOS search app" border="0" /></a>Google&#039;s feeling a bit nostalgic lately: in fact, today is the company&#039;s 15th anniversary. However, its look at the past is a fleeting thing, and Big G is very much focused on the future. To that end, Senior VP of Search, Amit Singhal just revealed a host of new features for search.</p><br clear="all"/>
